You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput microservice hangs indefinitely. Thread dumps reveal multiple threads are blocked on a `ConcurrentHashMap` operation. The following code is used to manage a hierarchical configuration cache: 

java
@Service
public class ConfigService {
    private final Map<String, String> configCache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    public String resolveConfig(String key) {
        return configCache.computeIfAbsent(key, k -> {
            if (k.startsWith("link:")) {
                return resolveConfig(k.substring(5));
            }
            return loadFromDatabase(k);
        });
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where an application experiences a slow memory leak in its custom event-sourcing layer. The following class is used as a high-performance buffer for processing `Event` objects before they are flushed to the database: 

java
public class CustomEventBuffer<T> {
    private T[] elements;
    private int size = 0;
    private int head = 0;

    public CustomEventBuffer(int capacity) {
        elements = (T[]) new Object[capacity];
    }

    public void add(T element) {
        elements[size++] = element;
    }

    public T poll() {
        if (size == 0) return null;
        T val = elements[head++];
        size--;
        return val;
    }
}
